# Classic Spring factories registration. Without a Zed language claiming
# `*.factories` this file reaches no language server at all, so its presence in
# the fixture is what makes that gap observable in a driven run.
#
# The registered class really does implement the factory type. Spring instantiates
# every entry during startup and fails the context on a mismatch, which would break
# the run/debug checks that boot this fixture.
org.springframework.context.ApplicationListener=\
  dev.zed.spring.fixture.GreetingStartupListener
